2. Take an array and a number that needs to be checked if present in the array. If number is present,print number is found along with the index
   at which it is present,else print number is not found

code :

import java.util.*;

public class MyClass {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        
        
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        boolean flag=true;
        int arr[] = {1,2,3,4,5};
        for(int i=0;i<=arr.length-1;i++){
            if(arr[i] == n){
                System.out.println(i+1);
                flag = true;
                break;
            }
            else{
                flag =false;
            }
            
        }
        if(flag == true){
                System.out.println("found");
            }
        else{
                System.out.println("Not found");
            }

    }
}
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

3.Take an array and a number that needs to be checked if present in the array. If number is present,print number is found along with the last index
   at which it is present,else print number is not found

code :

import java.util.*;

public class MyClass {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        
        int index=0;
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        boolean flag=true;
        int arr[] = {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,5,3,4,5};
        for(int i=0;i<=arr.length-1;i++){
            if(arr[i] == n){
                flag = true;
                index = i+1;
            }
            else{
                flag =false;
            }
            
        }
        if(flag == true){
            System.out.println(index);
            System.out.println("found");
            }
        else{
                System.out.println("Not found");
            }

    }
}

